BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:epq-session-mnvgnf4igit7x@epq-tutor-dashboard
DTSTAMP:20260414T020823ZZ
CREATED:20260412T074701ZZ
DTSTART;TZID=Asia/Shanghai:20260412T150000
DTEND;TZID=Asia/Shanghai:20260412T154000
SUMMARY:李东霖 (Vincent) · TA #1
DESCRIPTION:2026.04.12 TA Meeting 会议记录\nSA作业#1：表2填写\n以下为上次SA会议的摘要\nQuick re
 cap\nAustin conducted an initial consultation with Vincent about his EPQ (
 Extended Project Qualification) project\, which involves creating a shader
  pack for Minecraft. Vincent explained his plan to develop a shader pack w
 ith higher performance and advanced functions\, using OpenGL coding langua
 ge\, and Austin helped refine the project title to “Make a Shader Pack wit
 h High Performance and Advanced Functions for Minecraft.” They discussed t
 he project structure\, including the need for documentation\, research met
 hodology\, and presentation of evidence through screenshots and video demo
 nstrations. Austin introduced Vincent to the assessment criteria and marki
 ng grids in the student guidebook\, and assigned tasks for Vincent to comp
 lete before their next meeting\, including writing an introduction section
 \, working on Form 2 and Form 6\, and conducting initial research using th
 e provided reading log template.\nNext steps\n●vincent: Complete Form 2 (p
 roject authorization) this week\, including copying the updated project ti
 tle\, summarizing today’s meeting and feedback\, and commenting on any cha
 nges made to the project.\n●vincent: Begin maintaining Form 6 (project act
 ivity log)\, starting with logging today’s meeting and any subsequent EPQ-
 related activities\, including date\, activity\, duration\, and reflective
  comments.\n●vincent: Write an introduction section for the EPQ project th
 is week\, ensuring it introduces the project\, explains the topic’s import
 ance and interest\, and includes definitions of key terms for a non-specia
 list reader.\n●vincent: Start initial research on OpenGL\, computer graphi
 cs\, and related topics\, making notes and\, if applicable\, filling in th
 e provided reading log template for any sources consulted.\n●vincent: Revi
 ew the CRAAP principle document (sent via WeChat) and use it to analyze so
 urces for the reading log.\n●vincent: Meet with Austin at 3pm on 19th Apri
 l for the next check-in.\n\nSA作业#2：表6填写\nSA作业#3：Introduction部分写作\n写作大纲：\n作
 品：Minecraft光影包\nIntroduction写作部分(200-300 words)\n1.关键词定义：\na.“Minecraft”\n
 b.“光影包”（shaderpack)\n2.选题原因\na.应用图形学新技术\n3.特点\na.此光影包与其它的不同之处\n4.方法/如何去实现\
 na.OpenGL\nb.图形学理论\n\nSA作业#4：Reading log\nCRAAP文献分析方法\n●下次上课之前找到三篇论文，并且做CR
 AAP分析\n找什么样的论文？以下关键词：\n1.图形学/computer graphics\na.图形学文献综述/总览性文章 (fundament
 als of computer graphics)\n2.minecraft\na.之前光影包的作品设计\n3.资源：\n●光影包资源网站（因为渲染
 引擎更换所以暂时停更）\n○写在Reading list里，确保用英文写得规范且正式\n○说明为什么是可信并且可以参考的信息来源\n■e.g. 人数
 ，活跃度，产出的评价（下载量，视频播放量）\n\nCRAAP分析案例：Fundamentals of computer graphics\nCurr
 ency:	●Publication date: 2015/12/18\, fifth revision on 2022\n●still very 
 current\nRelevance: 	●directly relevant to the research\nAuthority:	●看一下作者
 的履历\nAccuracy:	●This is a very popular book\, so the information is relati
 vely reliable.\nPurpose:	●比较基础的图形学教材\n\n\n文献查询计划：在代码遇到问题的时候去寻找相应解决的文献\n●跟S
 A老师说明你的想法，并且解释你觉得这种做法比较合适
END:VEVENT
